headlines.description: Freshman Gary Trent Jr. had 22 points and tied a season high with 10 rebounds, and No. 4 Duke beat Notre Dame 88-66 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent, No. 4 Duke bounce back by routing Irish 88-66

headlines.description: Svi Mykhailiuk had 22 points to lead four Kansas players in double-figures, and the seventh-ranked Jayhawks beat Kansas State 70-56 on Monday night to retain sole possession of the Big 12 lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mykhailiuk leads No. 7 Kansas over Kansas State 70-56

video.headline: Mykhailiuk fuels Kansas past Kansas State

headlines.description: Charles Matthews scored 14 points, and No. 24 Michigan outlasted Northwestern 58-47 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 24 Michigan outlasts Northwestern 58-47

headlines.description: Desonta Bradford had a career-high 23 points and nine rebounds, Bo Hodges added 19 points and nine boards, and first-place East Tennessee State won its 13th straight with a 73-71 victory over The Citadel on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: ETSU extends 3rd longest active winning streak to 13 games

headlines.description: Rodney Chatman made a pair of free throws with 4.3 seconds left to lift Chattanooga over UNC Greensboro 87-85 in double overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chatman's shots help Chattanooga upset UNCG 87-85 in 2OT

headlines.description: Fletcher Magee scored 18 points while Trevor Stumpe and Nathan Hoover each scored 17 and Wofford beat Western Carolina 77-68 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magee heats up, Wofford downs Western Carolina 77-68

headlines.description: Tyler Nelson scored 32 points and Aidas Kavaliauskas had a double-double to help Fairfield beat Iona 103-100 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nelson scores 32, Fairfield beats Iona 103-100 in OT

headlines.description: Freshman Jordan Allen scored 26 points with a season-high seven 3-pointers and Rider beat Monmouth 92-85 on Monday night for its fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Freshman Allen scores 26, Rider tops Monmouth 92-85

headlines.description: Roman Penn scored 18 points, Ahsante Shivers had 14 points and 10 rebounds off the bench and Siena beat Saint Peter's 59-57 in triple overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siena grinds past St. Peter's 59-57 in triple overtime

headlines.description: Zach Johnson led six Florida Gulf Coast players in double figures with 16 points, Michael Gilmore had a double-double and the Eagles beat North Florida 103-70 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: FGCU pours it on North Florida for 103-70 rout

headlines.description: JD Notae made 2 of 3 free throws with 0.5 seconds left and finished with 20 points to help Jacksonville beat Stetson 68-67 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notae's FTs with 0.5 left lift Jacksonville over Stetson

headlines.description: Abdul Lewis had 20 points on 7-of-10 shooting and Anthony Tarke made 5 of 6 free throws in the final 16 seconds to help NJIT beat Kennesaw State 74-71 on Monday night after blowing a 21-point lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tarke's late free throws help NJIT beat Kennesaw State 74-71

headlines.description: Rob Marberry had a career-high 38 points to go with nine rebounds on Monday night and Lipscomb escaped at USC Upstate with a 110-106 win in double overtime.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lipscomb outlasts USC Upstate 110-106 in 2OT

headlines.description: Jermaine Marrow scored a career-high 35 points, tied a career high with 10 rebounds and had nine assists and Hampton beat Bethune-Cookman 80-69 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marrow scores 35 to help Hampton beat Bethune-Cookman

headlines.description: Jordan Cohen scored 19 points to help Lehigh hang on for a 71-67 victory over Holy Cross on Monday night after nearly blowing a 19-point lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lehigh nearly blows 19-point lead, tops Holy Cross 71-67

headlines.description: Damani Applewhite had 18 points and 12 rebounds, Patrell Rogers added 15 points and nine rebounds with five assists and South Carolina State beat Morgan State 74-59 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: South Carolina State beats Morgan State 74-59

headlines.description: Chad Andrews-Fulton had 16 points on Monday night and Coppin State survived without a field goal in the final two minutes to beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 71-68.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coppin State beats Maryland-Eastern Shore 71-68

headlines.description: Triston Chambers set career highs with eight 3-pointers and 34 points to help Samford beat VMI 93-79 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chambers' career-high 34 lead Samford over VMI 93-79

headlines.description: Tarkus Ferguson had 19 points, Dikembe Dixson and Godwin Boahen scored 13 apiece, and Illinois-Chicago beat Milwaukee 74-56 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Feguson, UIC beat Milwaukee 74-56, win fourth in a row

headlines.description: Nic Thomas scored 20 points and made all 12 of his foul shots -- 10 in the final 2:15 -- and Norfolk State beat Florida A&M 80-71 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas proves clutch, leads Norfolk St. past FAMU 80-71

headlines.description: Gary Blackston scored a career-high 32 points with eight rebounds and five assists and Prairie View A&M beat Alabama A&M 88-67 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blackston's 32 pts sends Prairie View A&M past Alabama A&M

headlines.description: Ivy Smith, Jr. had 26 points and nine rebounds, Nigel Ribeiro added 20 points, and Grambling beat Mississippi Valley State 92-89 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grambling avoids upset, beats MVSU 92-89 in OT

headlines.description: James Palmer Jr. scored 28 points and keyed a second-half comeback, as Nebraska rallied for a 74-63 victory over Wisconsin on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Palmer scores 28, Nebraska rallies past Wisconsin 74-63

headlines.description: Donte Clark scored 30 points and Derrick Bruce added 25 to help Texas Southern beat Alabama State 97-82 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clark scores 30 as Texas Southern beats Alabama St.

headlines.description: Terrance Banyard scored 16 points and Martaveous McKnight hit a jumper in the closing seconds to help Arkansas-Pine Bluff overcome a 19-point deficit to beat Jackson State 60-58 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McKnight's jumper gives UAPB a 60-58 win over Jackson State

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
